docs.abstract: The two clashed over bankruptcy policy more than a decade ago. But Joseph R. Biden Jr. now supports Elizabeth Warren’s plan that allows student debt to be relieved in bankruptcy.
docs.snippet: The two clashed over bankruptcy policy more than a decade ago. But Joseph R. Biden Jr. now supports Elizabeth Warren’s plan that allows student debt to be relieved in bankruptcy.
docs.lead_paragraph: Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr., who has battled with Senator Elizabeth Warren of Massachusetts in the past over the issue of bankruptcy, now supports a plan by Ms. Warren to make changes to the bankruptcy system, his presidential campaign confirmed on Saturday.

headline.main: Biden, Looking to Attract Progressives, Endorses Warren Bankruptcy Plan
headline.print_headline: Warren Bankruptcy Plan Gets Endorsement of Biden

byline.original: By Katie Glueck and Thomas Kaplan

docs.abstract: Florida, Illinois and Arizona pressed ahead with their presidential primary elections on Tuesday, but chaos and confusion in Illinois sent in-person turnout diving amid coronavirus fears.
docs.snippet: Florida, Illinois and Arizona pressed ahead with their presidential primary elections on Tuesday, but chaos and confusion in Illinois sent in-person turnout diving amid coronavirus fears.
docs.lead_paragraph: Voting in major cities in Illinois was rife with confusion on Tuesday and early turnout in many areas was significantly lower than expected, leading to complaints from poll workers and clashes between Chicago officials and the statehouse.

headline.main: Illinois Stumbles as States See Light Voter Turnout, With Many Ballots in the Mail

byline.original: By Nick Corasaniti, Stephanie Saul, Matt Stevens and Reid J. Epstein

docs.abstract: Participating in a healthy democracy isn’t supposed to be at odds with staying healthy. Today it is.
docs.snippet: Participating in a healthy democracy isn’t supposed to be at odds with staying healthy. Today it is.
docs.lead_paragraph: These are the instructions now, simple and bleak: Stay home if you can. Only essential personnel report for duty. Do not travel unless absolutely necessary.

headline.main: Are Voters ‘Essential Personnel’ During a Pandemic?
headline.print_headline: Despite the Risks, or Because of Them, an Essential Duty Is Fulfilled

docs.abstract: Governors of both parties have taken a lead role in confronting the crisis, asserting themselves in ways that have only highlighted the initial lack of seriousness from the White House.
docs.snippet: Governors of both parties have taken a lead role in confronting the crisis, asserting themselves in ways that have only highlighted the initial lack of seriousness from the White House.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — One day after President Trump told the nation’s governors on a conference call that he had been “watching a lot of you on television” dealing with the coronavirus, he proved it Tuesday morning by angrily tweeting at Michigan’s governor for saying on MSNBC that “the federal government did not take this seriously early enough.”

headline.main: Once Political B-Listers, Governors Lead Nation’s Coronavirus Response
headline.print_headline: In a Crisis, Governors Flexed Their Executive Muscles as the White House Balked

byline.original: By Jonathan Martin and Alexander Burns

docs.abstract: Former campaign workers for Michael R. Bloomberg’s presidential bid reacted angrily on Monday to news that they would not work through the November election, as expected.
docs.snippet: Former campaign workers for Michael R. Bloomberg’s presidential bid reacted angrily on Monday to news that they would not work through the November election, as expected.
docs.lead_paragraph: When the multibillionaire Michael R. Bloomberg hired an army of staff members for his presidential campaign, he lavished them with salaries that were nearly double what other candidates were paying. His campaign also promised something rivals could not match: job security through the general election, even if he dropped out of the race.

headline.main: Bloomberg’s Job Security Promises Are Falling Through, Campaign Workers Say
headline.print_headline: Promising Job Security, Bloomberg  Shifts Course

docs.abstract: Ms. Warren, a senator and former law professor, staked her campaign on fighting corruption and changing the rules of the economy.
docs.snippet: Ms. Warren, a senator and former law professor, staked her campaign on fighting corruption and changing the rules of the economy.
docs.lead_paragraph: CAMBRIDGE, Mass. — Senator Elizabeth Warren entered the 2020 race with expansive plans to use the federal government to remake American society, pressing to strip power and wealth from a moneyed class that she saw as fundamentally corrupting the country’s economic and political order.

headline.main: Elizabeth Warren, Once a Front-Runner, Drops Out of Presidential Race
headline.print_headline: Warren Exits, And Rivals Vie For Her Favor

docs.abstract: In an effort to raise the influence of female political leaders and female voters, the meeting aims to pressure the Democratic Party to place greater focus on issues faced by American women.
docs.snippet: In an effort to raise the influence of female political leaders and female voters, the meeting aims to pressure the Democratic Party to place greater focus on issues faced by American women.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A coalition of the country’s most prominent women’s advocacy groups will host a meeting of top female organizers, activists and officials on the eve of the Democratic National Convention in July, part of an effort to raise the influence of female political leaders and voters who make up the backbone of the party.

headline.main: Women’s Groups Will Host Summit Meeting Before D.N.C.
headline.print_headline: Women’s Groups to Gather On Eve of July Convention

docs.abstract: With an increasingly narrow path to the nomination, Mr. Sanders and his advisers were weighing his options amid a national health crisis.
docs.snippet: With an increasingly narrow path to the nomination, Mr. Sanders and his advisers were weighing his options amid a national health crisis.
docs.lead_paragraph: Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont was reassessing the future of his presidential bid on Wednesday after a crushing round of primary losses left him with no realistic path to the Democratic nomination and the 2020 race itself was on hold because of the coronavirus outbreak.

headline.main: Bernie Sanders Has No Realistic Chance to Win. Some Democrats Say, ‘It’s Over.’
headline.print_headline: Sanders Urged  To End His Run  As Path Erodes

docs.abstract: The former governor of Massachusetts carried out a long-shot primary campaign focused on appealing to moderate Republicans.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A day after President Trump officially racked up enough delegates to become the presumptive 2020 Republican nominee for president, former Gov. William F. Weld of Massachusetts, his last Republican challenger, ended his campaign.

headline.main: Bill Weld, Trump’s Last G.O.P. Challenger, Exits Presidential Race
